# field-ui architecture

**Signals-first:** All component inputs use `input()` / `input.required()`, state uses `signal()`, derived values use `computed()`. No `@Input()` decorators, no `ChangeDetectorRef`, no `OnChanges`. Host events use `host` metadata in `@Component`.

**Icon system:** `FieldIconComponent` (`<field-icon>`) renders icons by name (from `FieldIconRegistry`) or custom SVG. Built-in icons (menu, search, person, lock, info, close, check, eye) registered in `built-in-icons.ts`. Consumers can register additional icons via `FieldIconRegistry.register()`.

**Suggest panel:** `SuggestPanelComponent` (`<field-suggest-panel>`) is a standalone listbox with keyboard navigation (Arrow, Enter, Escape, Home, End), highlight tracking, and ARIA. The parent `FieldStandardComponent` owns filtering and open/close logic; the panel owns rendering and key handling.

**Tokens:** `_tokens.scss` is a barrel that `@use`s `_colors.scss`, `_typography.scss`, `_dimensions.scss`, `_dropdown.scss`. All values are CSS custom properties scoped to `:root` / `[data-theme]`. Playground imports via `@use '../../field-ui/src/lib/styles/tokens'`.
